            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">40x30x20cm | Double Wall | 15-20kg capacity</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-label text-primary font-bold text-sm mb-2">LARGE COMPONENTS (Engines, Transmissions)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">60x40x40cm | Triple Wall | 30-50kg capacity</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-label text-primary font-bold text-sm mb-2">MIXED PARTS KITS</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Custom modular boxes with dividers | Double Wall</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Common Questions About Automotive Parts Packaging</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">What's the difference between automotive and standard corrugated boxes?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Automotive boxes use thicker kraft paper (350–400 GSM) and reinforced flute design to handle vibration and impact during long highway journeys. Standard boxes work for light packaging but may fail with heavy mechanical components.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">How long does custom printing take on automotive carton boxes?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Standard lead time is 5–7 business days for custom printing. Urgent orders within Balakong and Klang Valley can be expedited to 48 hours. Contact us via WhatsApp to discuss your timeline.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Are your boxes suitable for international automotive shipping?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes. Our triple-wall boxes meet international shipping standards for automotive parts. We can accommodate humidity barriers and secure strapping for parts destined for ASEAN markets and beyond.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">What's the minimum order quantity for custom automotive boxes?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Minimum order is RM 1,000 in total value. You can mix and match sizes and designs within a single order. We're flexible with growing automotive suppliers in Selangor and across Malaysia.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Do you offer desiccant or silica gel inserts for moisture protection?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes, we partner with desiccant suppliers to add moisture-control packets inside carton boxes. This protects metal components from rust during tropical storage and long-distance shipping across Malaysia.</p>
